## Reflection — Day 5 Session 1

- def defines a function — it does not run it
- Parameters are the inputs a function receives
- return sends the result back to wherever the function was called
- Functions with conditionals inside make intelligent reusable tools
- Default parameters make functions flexible without requiring all inputs
- Functions can return multiple values at once
- Calling a function inside another function builds powerful toolkits
- One change to a function updates every place it is used


## Reflection — Day 5 Session 2

- A toolkit is a collection of small focused functions
- Each function does ONE job well
- Scoring functions return numbers that other functions can use
- Functions make complex analysis readable and organized
- The same function works on any site just by changing the input
- zone_counts dictionary counts how many times each zone appears
- .items() loops through both keys and values of a dictionary
- Building functions now means less repetition in pandas and R later
